					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In a demo, intro, or other program with limited interactivity, you have a lot more leeway than you have with a game. In a game, you have a lot of objects' state to keep in the NES's 2 KB of built-in work RAM, you have to make time for the OAM update, and you have to run AI and physics during the 'draw' time. In a demo, you don't.</div>

